Pre-Amyloid PET Disclosure

Source: R/data.R
PREAMYDISC.Rd

Pre-Amyloid PET Disclosure data. More information is available at https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Usage

data(PREAMYDISC)

Format

A data frame with 462 observations and 25 variables.

Source

https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Details

  • ORIGPROT character Original study protocol , with options: ADNI4, ADNI2, ADNIGO, ADNI3, ADNI1

  • COLPROT factor Study protocol of data collection , with factor levels: ADNI1, ADNIGO, ADNI2, ADNI3, ADNI4

  • PTID character Participant ID

  • RID numeric Participant roster ID Range value: 21, ..., 10618

  • VISCODE character Visit code , with options: 4_bl, 4_init, 4_m12

  • VISCODE2 character Translated visit code

  • VISDATE Registry EXAMDATE on matching VISCODE Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • PETLEARN character Have you ever learned the result of a PET (positron emission tomography) scan that measures brain amyloid? This may also have been referred to as an "amyloid PET scan" or a "brain amyloid scan." 0=No; 1=Yes; 99=I don't know Decoded Value: Yes

  • PETRESULT character If yes, what was your amyloid PET scan result? 0=Not Elevated; 1=Elevated; 99=I don't know Decoded Value: Yes

  • RISKAD character For CN/MCI: If yes, did your amyloid PET scan result indicate that you have an increased risk for developing Alzheimer's disease dementia? 0=No, my amyloid PET scan result did not indicate an increased risk for Alzheimer's disease dementia.; 1=Yes, my amyloid PET scan result indicated an increased risk for Alzheimer's disease dementia.; 2=Not applicable (For DEM); 99=I don't know Decoded Value: Yes

  • CONSAD character For dementia: If yes, was your amyloid PET scan result consistent with Alzheimer's disease dementia? 0=No, my amyloid PET scan result was not consistent with Alzheimer's disease; 1=Yes, my amyloid PET scan result was consistent with Alzheimer's disease; 2=Not applicable (For CN/MCI); 99=I don't know Decoded Value: Yes

  • DESCBHC character Which of the terms best describes what you've been told about your brain health and cognition? 1="I am cognitively unimpaired"; 2="I have mild cognitive impairment"; 3="I have dementia"; 4=Not applicable (For CN/MCI); 99=Don't remember/ Don't know Decoded Value: Yes

  • RESULT character What do you think the result of your amyloid PET scan will be? 0=Not Elevated; 1=Elevated; 99=I don't know Decoded Value: Yes

  • CONFLVL numeric On a scale of 0-100%, how confident are you that's what your result will be? Range value: 0, ..., 100

  • DEVDEMAD numeric On a scale of 0-100%, where 0% is no chance and 100% is definite, what do you think is your chance of developing dementia caused by Alzheimer's disease in your lifetime? Range value: 0, ..., 100

  • DEMADLVL character Would you say that your risk of developing dementia caused by Alzheimer's disease is very low (1), low (2), average (3), high (4), or very high (5)? 1=very low (1); 2=low (2); 3=average (3); 4=high (4); 5=very high (5); 6=Not applicable (For DEM) Decoded Value: Yes

  • DEMADAGE character What do you think your chances are of developing dementia caused by Alzheimer's disease compared to others your age? Much lower (1), A little lower (2), The same (3), A little higher (4), Much higher (5) 1=much lower (1); 2=a little lower (2); 3=the same (3); 4=a little higher (4); 5=much higher (5); 6=Not applicable (For DEM) Decoded Value: Yes

  • ID numeric Record ID Range value: 1285, ..., 82217

  • SITEID numeric Site ID Range value: 2, ..., 941

  • USERDATE User Create Date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • USERDATE2 User Last Modify Date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • DD_CRF_VERSION_LABEL character CRF Version Label , with options: v1

  • LANGUAGE_CODE character Language Code e=English Decoded Value: Yes

  • HAS_QC_ERROR character Has Quality Check Error 0=Does not have QC error or QC error has been approved; 1=Has QC error Decoded Value: Yes

  • update_stamp POSIXct: YYY-MM-DD
